commText: Dhawan and Bairstow are at the crease. Dhawan is on strike. Khaleel Ahmed will open the attack
Khaleel Ahmed to Dhawan, FOUR, short and wide outside off, perfect for Dhawan who gets on top of the bounce, cuts it wide of backward point
Khaleel Ahmed to Dhawan, no run, short of length just outside off, Dhawan punches to cover who gets across and cuts it off with a dive

Khaleel Ahmed to Dhawan, FOUR, fine shot. Full outside off, Dhawan drives late and opens the face of the bat to get it wide of backward point, fine square drive and gives deep backward point no chance
Khaleel Ahmed to Dhawan, 1 run, goes wide of the crease and angles it full on middle-stump, flicked away to deep backward square leg
Sun shining brightly still and lights on as well. That's quite weird.

Khaleel Ahmed to Bairstow, FOUR, third four of the over. A short of length delivery outside off, angling away from Bairstow who opens the face of the bat and runs it wide of the wide slip, runs away wide of third man

Khaleel Ahmed to Bairstow, FOUR, great start for PBKS. Full on off, Bairstow gets forward and drives wide of cover, beats the dive, runs away to the fence. 17 off the over and DC already on the back foot
Ishant Sharma, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Ishant to Dhawan, wide, way outside off, full and there's swing for Ishant but the line is wrong, left alone
Ishant is straightaway coming from round the wicket to Dhawan. A wide slip in too.
Ishant to Dhawan, wide, full and again too wide outside off despite the swing on it, left alone and another wide

Ishant to Dhawan, FOUR, Dhawan is on fire already. He gives the charge and slashes the back of a length delivery outside off, wide of point, that's trademark Dhawan. Hang on - replays show that Axar at point did not pick it, despite sunglasses on, reacted late and the ball went under his hands, without even touching them. Was definitely catchable
Ishant to Dhawan, wide, another wide outside off, Ishant can't get his radar right
Ishant to Dhawan, no run, fullish outside off, Dhawan pulls the bat inside the line as he lets it go, swung away too
Ishant to Dhawan, no run, Ishant tucks up Dhawan with a short of length delivery as he comes down the track, looks to defend, off the thick outer half of the bat, rolls to cover
Ishant to Dhawan, no run, short of length on off, Dhawan again steps out but defends it to point

Ishant to Dhawan, no run, only Ishant is interested for LBW. Dhawan shuffles across a long way and misses the flick to a leg-stump delivery, looks close and one has to check HawkEye for what happens next. Pant dives to his right to stop it and they don't take the review
Ishant to Dhawan, 1 run, full outside off, Dhawan is early into the drive, spoons it wide of cover and takes a run
Mitchell Marsh, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Mitchell Marsh to Dhawan, FOUR, in the air and wide of the diving backward point. Full and wide outside off, Dhawan slices the square drive and just about eludes the fielder to his left
Mitchell Marsh to Dhawan, 1 run, full on the stumps, pushed past Bairstow for one
Mitchell Marsh to Bairstow, 1 run, short of length on off, pushed to mid-on for a quick single

Mitchell Marsh to Dhawan, 2 runs, slower ball full outside off, Dhawan throws the bat on the square drive, again hits it in the air, wide of backward point and Warner at deep backward point on the dive, fumbles but recovers quickly to collect
Mitchell Marsh to Dhawan, no run, short of length and tight on off, Dhawan gets right behind the line to defend
Mitchell Marsh to Dhawan, 1 run, slower ball full outside off, driven to sweeper cover and straight to the fielder
Ishant to Dhawan, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Ishant to Dhawan, out Bowled!! Ishant knocks Dhawan over. Dhawan was getting too aggressive, comes down the track to swipe at a length delivery on the stumps, misses and the stumps are disturbed. DC needed that early wicket and they have got it. Dhawan b Ishant 22(16) [4s-4]
Prabhsimran Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Ishant to Prabhsimran, FOUR, thick outside-edge and there's no slip either. A short of length delivery on off, Prabhsimran is opened up on the defence, thick outside-edge flies away wide of short third man, to his left and four
A wide slip in now.

Ishant to Prabhsimran, FOUR, Prabhsimran does not get all of it but gets it wide of mid-off. He comes down the track and drives on the rise, wide of cover and beats mid-off to his left on the dive as well
Ishant to Prabhsimran, no run, short of length outside off, punched to cover
A run-out check and Bairstow is gone.
Ishant to Prabhsimran, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Ishant to Prabhsimran, out Bairstow Run Out!! Second wicket of the over. Unfortunate one but it happens in this game. Prabhsimran comes down the track and punches the drive, Ishant bends low and gets a fingertip on it, Bairstow is backing up too far, can't get back as the ball hits the stumps. Ishant knew it as soon as he got up when the stumps were disturbed. DC right back in this. Bairstow run out (Ishant) 9(3) [4s-2]
Sam Curran, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Ishant to Prabhsimran, no run, fullish outside off, Prabhsimran gets forward and pushes it back, was in the air and it's short of Ishant on his followthrough
Khaleel Ahmed [1.0-0-17-0] is back into the attack
Khaleel Ahmed to Sam Curran, no run, short of length and tight on off, defended back
Khaleel Ahmed to Sam Curran, no run, good inswinging yorker on off, dug out back

Khaleel Ahmed to Sam Curran, 2 runs, full and shaping back in to off, Sam Curran gets forward to drive and it's a thick inside-edge to the deep backward square leg region, the ball dribbles slowly, so they take two
Khaleel Ahmed to Sam Curran, 1 run, back of a length outside off, Sam Curran punches it wide of cover
Khaleel Ahmed round the wicket.
Khaleel Ahmed to Prabhsimran, FOUR, short of length and angling into Prabhsimran who goes on the back foot and pulls over mid-wicket, no-one at deep mid-wicket and runs away
Khaleel Ahmed to Prabhsimran, FOUR, Prabhsimran wants to be aggressive as well. He comes down the track and drives the full delivery wide of cover, got to the pitch and put it away

Match Highlights - Over (1-5) * Both Dhawan get going with 2 fours each in a 17-run opening over from Khaleel * Dhawan continues to find the boundaries * Ishant strikes for DC, sends back Dhawan for a 16-ball 22 * Prabhsimran gets going with a couple of boundaries * Jonny Bairstow gets run-out at the non-striker's end for 9 * Khaleel concedes 11 run sin the 5th over
Mitchell Marsh [1.0-0-9-0] is back into the attack
Shikhar vs Ishant in IPL: 8 inns 38 balls 41 runs 4 dismissals Avg 10.25 SR 107.89
Mitchell Marsh to Sam Curran, FOUR, cross-seam full delivery outside off, Sam Curran gets forward and thrashes that wide of cover, was in the slot and put away
Mitchell Marsh to Sam Curran, 1 run, short of length on middle, nudged to deep square leg

Mitchell Marsh to Prabhsimran, 1 run, slower good length delivery on middle, flicked towards deep mid-wicket and Ishant twists his right ankle and is down in pain, after trying to field that. The physio is out to have a look
Now Ishant is being helped off the field, he is hobbling off. Bad news for DC. Pravin Dubey is the sub.
Mitchell Marsh to Sam Curran, no run, full outside off, driven straight to the fielder at cover
Mitchell Marsh to Sam Curran, no run, full slower ball outside off, steered to backward point and Prabhsimran is halfway down, sent back and Prabhsimran is back
Mitchell Marsh to Sam Curran, 1 run, short and wide outside off, Sam Curran cuts hard and straight to the fielder at sweeper cover
Axar Patel, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Axar vs Punjab Kings: 8 mat 11 wkts Avg 14.73 ER 5.40 Best 2/10
Axar to Sam Curran, 1 run, fullish on the stumps, clipped to deep mid-wicket and it's just one
Axar convinces Pant to take the review for LBW. Impact is ump's call and wickets is missing. DC lose a review.

Axar to Prabhsimran, leg byes, 1 run, DC lose a review. Prabhsimran comes down the track to drive, misses the drifting in delivery, it strikes him on the pad, loud shout and Axar convinces Pant for the review. Impact is ump's call and it's missing leg-stump
Axar to Sam Curran, 2 runs, flat length delivery on off, whipped wide of long-on for two
Axar to Sam Curran, 1 run, slower and tossed up on the stumps, Sam Curran flicks through the vacant mid-wicket area
Prabhsimran vs spin in IPL 2023: 79 balls 124 runs Avg 62.00 SR 156.96
Axar to Prabhsimran, 1 run, short of length and drifting into leg-stump, turned to deep square leg
Axar to Sam Curran, 1 run, flat back of a length outside off, punched to long-off
Kuldeep Yadav, comes into the attack
Kuldeep Yadav to Sam Curran, 1 run, good length on the stumps, Sam Curran punches to long-on
Kuldeep Yadav to Prabhsimran, 1 run, good adjustment from Prabhsimran, Kuldeep Yadav knew he was coming down, so bowled it full and wide outside off, Prabhsimran flat-bats it straight down the ground
Kuldeep Yadav to Sam Curran, 1 run, tossed up and Sam Curran comes down the track to loft on the bounce to long-on
Kuldeep Yadav to Prabhsimran, 1 run, flat and wide length ball outside off, flat-batted to long-off
Kuldeep Yadav to Sam Curran, FOUR, fraction short and the back of a length delivery is on leg-stump, Sam Curran goes on the back foot to pull between deep square leg and deep mid-wicket
Kuldeep Yadav to Sam Curran, no run, flat good length on the stumps, tucked to mid-wicket
Timeout! This partnership has shown urgency and they are not afraid to even go after Kuldeep Yadav. Game nicely poised at this stage.
Axar to Prabhsimran, 1 run, Prabhsimran comes down the track and lofts but it's off the thick inside half, falls in front of long-on
Axar to Sam Curran, 1 run, flat back of a length outside off, punched to long-on
Axar to Prabhsimran, FOUR, fine shot. Prabhsimran makes room and hammers the length ball from middle-stump, past the diving extra-cover and wide long-off of Warner
Axar to Prabhsimran, 1 run, back of a length on middle, tucked to deep square leg
Axar to Sam Curran, 1 run, fullish on the stumps, pushed to long-on
Axar to Prabhsimran, no run, full outside off, defended to cover
Kuldeep Yadav to Sam Curran, leg byes, 1 run, tossed up outside the leg-stump, Sam Curran looks to flick, misses, takes a legbye
Kuldeep Yadav to Prabhsimran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Kuldeep Yadav to Prabhsimran, out Caught by Warner!! The googly and full outside off, Prabhsimran goes for the loft as it's in the slot, but does not get enough to clear Warner at long-on. Big boundaries here and that's an easy catch. Prabhsimran c Warner b Kuldeep Yadav 26(17) [4s-5]
Jitesh Sharma, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Kuldeep Yadav to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, tossed up full outside off, Jitesh Sharma gets forward to drive, in the air but wide of cover
Kuldeep Yadav to Sam Curran, 1 run, tossed up full outside off, driven to cover, and hit hard, so the fielder can only parry it away
Kuldeep Yadav to Jitesh Sharma, no run, good delivery. Slides on from a good length just outside off, Jitesh Sharma goes on the back foot to push and does well not to nick it, good take too
Kuldeep Yadav to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, tossed up full on the stumps, Jitesh Sharma gets forward to drive wristily to long-on

Match Highlights - Over (6-10) * Ishant rolls his ankle over and has had to be helped away off the field * Prabhsimran survives a close LBW review off Axar Patel on 17 * Kuldeep Yadav concedes 8 runs in his opening over * Prabhsimran holes out to long-on off Kuldeep, OUT for 26
Sumit Kumar, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
A stumping appeal sent upstairs. A flat line on UltraEdge. Just back in time.

Sumit Kumar to Jitesh Sharma, no run, Jitesh Sharma did well to get back. A short of length delivery down leg, he overbalances on the flick and misses, Pant is a tad late to get it back on to the stumps, that allows Jitesh to get back in
Sumit Kumar to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, fullish outside off, steered with an open face to short third man
Sumit Kumar round the wicket.
Sumit Kumar to Sam Curran, FOUR, a slower short of length delivery outside off, too easy for Sam Curran who pulls it disdainfully to the deep mid-wicket fence
Sumit Kumar to Sam Curran, 1 run, slower ball on a good length, tapped in front of backward point for one
Sumit Kumar to Jitesh Sharma, FOUR, mediocre bowling this. A slower short of length delivery outside off, with so much width, carved over cover
Sumit Kumar to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, fullish on the stumps, Jitesh Sharma gets forward to drive to long-on with a full face
Kuldeep Yadav to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, slower and wider outside off, Jitesh Sharma gets low to sweep, toe-ended to short third man and they go for a quick single
Kuldeep Yadav to Sam Curran, 1 run, good length and no turn on middle-stump, tucked wide of mid-wicket
Another stumping appeal and sent upstairs. Gone now.
Kuldeep Yadav to Jitesh Sharma, THATS OUT!! Stumped!!

Kuldeep Yadav to Jitesh Sharma, out Stumped!! Wild from Jitesh Sharma and the momentum of the shot drags him outside his crease. The tossed up googly outside off, Jitesh Sharma tries a big reverse-sweep and misses, Pant does the rest. Jitesh was well out too. Jitesh Sharma st Pant b Kuldeep Yadav 9(9) [4s-1]
Liam Livingstone, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Kuldeep Yadav to Livingstone, 1 run, tossed up full on leg-stump, flicked through backward square leg for one
Kuldeep Yadav to Sam Curran, 1 run, slower and on leg-stump, nudged through the square leg region
Slip and a leg-slip in.
Kuldeep Yadav to Livingstone, 1 run, flighted delivery full on the stumps, Livingstone gets forward to drive wristily down to long-on
Axar Patel [2.0-0-14-0] is back into the attack
Axar to Livingstone, 1 run, flat and drifting into leg-stump, tucked to deep mid-wicket
Axar to Sam Curran, 2 runs, superb from Warner at long-on, Sam Curran comes down the track and punches it hard and Warner sprints and dives to his right, comes up with the ball, saves two
Axar to Sam Curran, 1 run, a dart on a length outside off, Sam Curran reaches for it to cut and gets it wide of backward point
Axar to Livingstone, no run, drifts in on a back of a length on off, tucks up Livingstone who pushes it back
Axar to Livingstone, no run
Axar to Livingstone, 1 run, tossed up full on off, flicked away to deep square leg
Kuldeep Yadav to Livingstone, 1 run, slower and the googly outside off, Livingstone mistimes the cut wide of cover, they take a quick single
Kuldeep Yadav to Sam Curran, 1 run, dropped by Stubbs at long-on. Sam Curran comes down the track and lofts, Stubbs runs to his right and gets low to catch, but drops it, should have been taken
Kuldeep Yadav round the wicket.
Kuldeep Yadav to Livingstone, 1 run, good length on middle-stump, tucked to deep mid-wicket
Kuldeep Yadav to Sam Curran, no run, tossed up slower and full on off, driven to cover, was in the air but short of the fielder
Kuldeep Yadav to Sam Curran, no run, flat good length on the stumps, Sam Curran makes room to cut but is cramped, bunts it back
Kuldeep Yadav to Sam Curran, 1 run, good length and no spin on the stumps, punched to long-on
Kuldeep Yadav is off the field. Not sure why.
Mitchell Marsh [2.0-0-16-0] is back into the attack
Mitchell Marsh to Sam Curran, FOUR, slower and wider outside off, width for Sam Curran who thrashes it wide of sweeper cover, runs away
Mitchell Marsh to Sam Curran, no run, short outside off, Sam Curran tries to ramp and misses
Mitchell Marsh to Sam Curran, FOUR, slower and shorter outside the leg-stump, Sam Curran gets inside the line and pulls to the deep backward square leg fence, poor bowling this
Mitchell Marsh to Sam Curran, wide, way outside off and nearly doesn't land on the cut-strip. Wide called
Mitchell Marsh to Sam Curran, 2 runs, short of length on off, whipped wide of deep mid-wicket for two
Mitchell Marsh round the wicket.
Mitchell Marsh to Sam Curran, 1 run, short of length outside off, punched down to long-on

Mitchell Marsh to Livingstone, SIX, expensive over and PBKS are favorites from here. A slower ball on a length outside off, Livingstone mows it massively and into the crowd at deep mid-wicket. That is a typical Livingstone shot

Match Highlights - Over (10-15) * Jitesh survives a close shout for a stumping off Sumi Kumar on 2 *  Two boundaries in the over as Sumit concedes 11 runs in the 11th over * Second wicket for Kuldeep, Jitesh gets stumped for 9 * Kuldeep ends a fine evening with the ball, 2/20 from his 4 overs * Mitchell Marsh concedes 18 runs in the 15th over
Axar Patel [3.0-0-19-0] is back into the attack
Axar to Sam Curran, 1 run, short of length on off, punched to long-on
Axar to Livingstone, 1 run, drifting in on a length on middle, tucked to deep mid-wicket
Axar to Sam Curran, 2 runs, a dart on a length outside off, Sam Curran smashes the cut but Kumar at extra-cover dives to his right and parries it to sweeper cover, saves two
Axar to Sam Curran, 1 run, 50 for Sam Curran. A good length delivery on off, pushed down to long-on
Axar to Livingstone, no run, tough chance and Pant drops it. Slower and tossed up outside off, Livingstone gets forward to drive, thick inside-edge and Pant can't hang on
Axar to Livingstone, 1 run, tossed up full outside off, Livingstone gets forward to drive to sweeper cover
Timeout! PBKS should win this but you never know in this format, especially in the IPL, more so.
Khaleel Ahmed [2.0-0-28-0] is back into the attack
Khaleel Ahmed to Livingstone, 1 run, slower short of length delivery outside off, cut hard and straight to sweeper cover
Khaleel Ahmed to Sam Curran, no run, slower short of length delivery on the stumps, Sam Curran makes room and defends it, wants a run near the stumps, Livingstone sends him back
Khaleel Ahmed to Sam Curran, 1 run, slower ball full on the stumps, hoicked to deep mid-wicket
Khaleel Ahmed to Livingstone, FOUR, just wide of both Pant and the diving short third man. Slower and fuller outside off, Livingstone drives and the thick outside-edge helps him get away, so lucky
Khaleel Ahmed to Livingstone, FOUR, Livingstone gets four but he is not happy. Length delivery on the stumps, Livingstone swings it wide of short fine-leg and he wanted more meat on that shot
Khaleel Ahmed to Livingstone, 1 run, full outside off, Livingstone mistimes the drive to long-off
Mitchell Marsh [3.0-0-34-0] is back into the attack
Mitchell Marsh to Livingstone, 1 run, short of length outside off, Livingstone splices the pull, down to mid-on which is vacant
Mitchell Marsh to Sam Curran, SIX, Mitchell Marsh has been very expensive tonight. A slower short delivery at Sam Curran who gets inside the line and pulls over fine-leg, flies into the crowd
Mitchell Marsh to Sam Curran, FOUR, now on the off-side, a short of length delivery outside off, cut in the air and wide of backward point, races away
Mitchell Marsh to Sam Curran, no run, fullish on the stumps, pushed back and Mitchell Marsh gets across and cuts it off to his left
Mitchell Marsh to Sam Curran, 1 run, short of length outside off, flat-batted to mid-off
Mitchell Marsh to Livingstone, SIX, terrible bowling. A short delivery at the tall Livingstone who sends the pull almost into the first tier at fine-leg, Mitchell Marsh ends with 0/52
Khaleel Ahmed to Sam Curran, 1 run, slower and fuller on the stumps, swung away to fine-leg
Khaleel Ahmed to Livingstone, 1 run, full outside off, Livingstone mistimes the drive to long-on
Khaleel Ahmed to Sam Curran, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Khaleel Ahmed to Sam Curran, out Bowled!! Sam Curran swings and misses. The slower ball off-cutter on a length on the stumps, beats the swing and falls on the stumps. A consolation wicket? Sam Curran b Khaleel Ahmed 63(47) [4s-6 6s-1]
Shashank Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Khaleel Ahmed to Shashank Singh, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Khaleel Ahmed to Shashank Singh, out Caught by Pant!! Two in two. Dug in short at Shashank Singh who swivels to pull, bit of glove and bit of bat, lobs to Pant who takes it and gestures that this is what I want from you to the bowler. Khaleel Ahmed on a hat-trick now. Shashank Singh c Pant b Khaleel Ahmed 0(1)
Harpreet Brar, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Khaleel Ahmed to Harpreet Brar, no run, short of length outside off, Harpreet Brar tries to run it down and misses, a dot

Khaleel Ahmed to Harpreet Brar, 2 runs, dropped by Warner at long-on. Deadpan expressions from Ponting and Ganguly in the DC dugout. A short of length delivery outside off, flat-batted in the air, Warner runs in and drops a simple catch. That is a big chance
Six needed off the last over and Sumit Kumar to bowl it. Pant has a few words to the bowler.
Sumit Kumar [1.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Sumit Kumar to Livingstone, wide, a wide outside off to begin, sloppy stuff, the short ball dug in goes wrong
Sumit Kumar to Livingstone, wide, another wide as this is dug in, way too short and left alone. Poor bowling
4 from 6. PBKS' to lose it from here.
Sumit Kumar to Livingstone, no run, a wide length delivery outside off, scythed straight to the fielder at extra-cover

Sumit Kumar to Livingstone, SIX, Livingstone finishes it off. A fullish delivery outside off, swung away over mid-wicket and it carries all the way. The PBKS camp are elated as Livingstone and Shai Hope share a laugh

19:19 Local Time, 13:49 GMT, 19:19 IST: PBKS begin on a winning note. Contrary to expectations, the pitch did not slow down and played perfectly till the end. Dhawan and Bairstow started off with a flurry but they went in quick succession. Sam Curran at 4 and the impact player Prabhsimran shared a nice little stand for the third wicket. DC did not help themselves with dropped chances and it proved costly. Curran was dropped on 33 and at the end Harpreet Brar by Warner. Curran went after his fifty and Khaleel introduced some excitement in the penultimate over with 2 wickets and a dropped catch but Livingstone finished it off. A measured chase this from PBKS who were helped by Ishant hobbling off. Ishant's overs had to be covered up and Sumit Kumar was no match there. Also Mitch Marsh had a forgettable day with the ball. Stay tuned for the presentation...

Rishabh Pant | DC captain: I think Ishant's injury was clearly evident in the field, we were already one bowler short because of our batting, Abishek Porel did well to give us those extra runs, but we were always one bowler short. The boys did well to drag us back into the match at various stages. Was pretty nervous (on his comeback), there was a bit of tension, but I started to enjoy myself. No excuses, having a bowler short was never good, but credit to PKBS for the way they played. He's pretty new (on Porel), 3rd or 4th game (for him), the way he batted was very special, looking forward to more from him as the season moves forward.

Liam Livingstone: We did really well. Our spinners dragged it really well. The pitch got better as the lights came on. The toss helped I guess. Just the first game. The bowlers have done well. We have got a very good outfit. To restrict them to what they got, was a good effort. We expected the pitch to get better and it did. It has been a tough sort of year for me. The group has a lot of confidence in me. I have done some work on my game in the last 4 weeks. Hopefully the start of a good tournament for us. Sam got runs for us. The middle order would be fun.

Stats round-up by Deepu Narayanan Pace vs spin in PK innings Spin: 2/45 in 8 overs (ER 5.63) Pace: 3/130 in 11.2 overs (ER 11.47) Punjab Kings in their season openers since 2017 2017: Won 2018: Won 2019: Won 2020: Tied (Lost Super Over) 2021: Won 2022: Won 2023: Won 2024: Won

Shikhar Dhawan | PBKS captain: It feels great, I was happy to be on the ground. After the last IPL, I'm playing such a high competitive cricket, I was a bit nervous. [on the chat at the innings break] That time I did not chat with anyone as I was supposed to go for batting. The bowlers need their space, so we will chat tomorrow and learn and get better. We leaked a few extra runs, of course first match of the season and nerves are there. I feel under lights the wicket got better and Sam played an amazing innings and Livi finished it off. I didn't know much records here, it's a new ground. Did not focus much. We practised in the day and under lights as well. Wanted the other team to use their brains on how to go here.

Sam Curran | Player of the Match: Really pleased. Amazing way to start the tournament on our new homeground, nothing better. They were, those two are world-class bowlers and played a lot of cricket for India but we knew if we could take it deep, we had a chance. To bat with my great mate Livi at the other end was special. At that stage I had to take those risks and thankfully luck was on my side. The wicket got slightly better under lights, the ball was travelling and not much spin and pace was coming on. [on him bowling just one over] We have got some great options this season and nice additions, maybe in Bangalore it will be a different thing, most importantly we got the win.
That's it for game 1 on this Saturday. We have the other game up and running between KKR and SRH. Hop tabs to catch us there. For now it's goodbye and tata from here.
